						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1438, Dhātu, Āshāḍha, ba. 30, Ādivāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1516 June 29, Sunday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇadēvarāya-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that the king exempted the donees of the <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> village <hi rend="bold">Kaṇiyakallu</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Rāyadurga-[sīme]</hi> from taxes and permitted them to enjoy the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāya</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmādāya</hi> lands without any disturbance.</p>						

						</summary>
